Figs. 73–85
.

Postpedal segments. Intermediate tergite with posterior margin strongly convex (
Fig. 94
), intermediate sternite with posterior margin nearly straight (
Fig. 95
). Posterior margin of first genital sternite concave (
Fig. 95
). Gonopods apparently uniarticulate (suture between the presumptive basal and distal articles not evident), bearing ca. 25 setae (
Fig. 97
); penis dorsally with 3 + 3 apical setae (
Fig. 98
). Anal organs absent.

